<p>Among the sprinting at BADCamp was the big kick-off of the <a href="https://groups.drupal.org/imp">Migrate in Core</a> initiative. Additionally, the CMI folks put together a <a href="https://drupal.org/node/2121751">concrete battleplan for finishing the configuration system</a>.</p>
<p>This also led to <a href="https://drupal.org/developing/api/8">creating overview/example API documentation for Drupal 8</a> this month, including <a href="https://drupal.org/node/2122071">routing system</a>, <a href="https://drupal.org/node/1667894">configuration system</a>, and the <a href="https://drupal.org/developing/api/entity">entity system</a>. These are now a part of the new <a href="https://drupal.org/drupal-8.0">Drupal 8.0 landing page</a>, also created in October.</p>
